# Supabase — RPC Only (No Direct Table Reads)

Since migration `006_secure_all_reads`, all RLS open-read policies have been removed.
Direct `supabase.from("table").select(...)` on protected tables returns `[]` silently.

## Rule: NEVER query tables directly from the frontend

❌ Forbidden:
```js
supabase.from("shibuts").select(...)
supabase.from("guards").select(...)
supabase.from("outposts").select(...)
supabase.from("shifts").select(...)
supabase.from("shift_requests").select(...)
supabase.from("system_messages").select(...)
```

✅ Always use the matching RPC:
```js
const creds = getCredentials(); // from "@/services/authCredentials"

supabase.rpc("rpc_get_shibuts_by_camp",    { ...creds, p_camp_id, p_start_ts, p_end_ts })
supabase.rpc("rpc_get_guards_by_camp",     { ...creds, p_camp_id })
supabase.rpc("rpc_get_outposts_by_camp",   { ...creds, p_camp_id })
supabase.rpc("rpc_get_shifts_by_outpost",  { ...creds, p_outpost_id })
supabase.rpc("rpc_get_shift_requests_by_camp", { ...creds, p_camp_id })
supabase.rpc("rpc_get_system_messages",    { ...creds, p_camp_id })
```

## Pattern for every new service function

```js
import { supabase } from "./supabaseClient";
import { getCredentials } from "./authCredentials";

export async function myNewDataFetcher(campId) {
  const creds = getCredentials();
  const { data, error } = await supabase.rpc("rpc_...", {
    ...creds,
    p_camp_id: campId,
  });
  if (error) throw error;
  return data;
}
```

## Adding a new data access need?

If no matching RPC exists yet:
1. Add a new `SECURITY DEFINER` function to `supabase/migrations/NNN_....sql`
2. `GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION ... TO anon`
3. Call it from the service via `supabase.rpc(...)`

Never add direct-read RLS policies back — the RPC pattern is the security boundary.
